It seems the `file` command is not available. Let me try to check the image properties using ImageMagick's `identify` command instead.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The `file` command is not available. I'll use ImageMagick's `identify` command to check the colorspace of one of the keyframes.",
  "plan": "Use `identify` to check the colorspace of keyframes_001.png. If it's grayscale, the output should indicate 'Gray' or 'sRGB' (though sRGB would be less ideal, it could still work for object detection).",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "identify -verbose /root/keyframes_001.png | grep Colorspace\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
```
